# Playback Architecture Rules

Read `docs/sets-video-architecture-freeze.md` (FROZEN Sets/Video rules), `docs/playback-architecture.md`, and `.cursor/rules/playback-reliability-protocol.mdc` before any playback work.

**Priority:** Playback reliability > Features > UI polish > Refactoring

## Layer boundaries (mandatory)

```
UI components → playback-actions → playback-store → global-player-engine → providers
```

## UI layer (`src/components`, `src/app`)

**Allowed:**
- `usePlaybackStore` selectors (read-only state)
- `playback-actions` dispatchers (`playItem`, `handlePlaybackSurfaceClick`, `seekTo`, etc.)
- `useCardPlayback` hook (thin wrapper over actions)

**Forbidden:**
- Import `global-player-engine`, `spotify-embed-api`, `youtube-embed-api`
- `document.createElement('audio'|'iframe')` for playback
- Local `useState` for `isPlaying`, `currentTime`, `duration`, or active track
- Duplicate click policy (play/pause/open) — use `handlePlaybackSurfaceClick`

## Store (`playback-store.ts`)

- Sole module that imports `globalPlayerEngine`
- Engine listener is the **only** writer for transport state (`isPlaying`, `currentTime`, etc.)
- Store actions set session fields (`currentTrack`, `queue`, `detailsOpen`) and forward commands

## Engine (`global-player-engine.ts`)

- Singleton; mount once; never torn down on route change
- Only layer that creates/destroys media elements

## Adding new playback UI

1. Read state from `usePlaybackStore`
2. Dispatch via `playback-actions.ts`
3. Add contract test in `tests/playback/contract.test.ts`
4. Run `npm run test:playback` and `npm run audit:playback-arch`

## UI refinement phase

UI redesign is **allowed and expected**. See `.cursor/rules/ui-refinement-phase.mdc`.

Protected backend files must not change without a reproducible playback bug.
